If you have 3 zones and want “run in any of them”

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: multi-zone-demo
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: multi-zone-demo
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: multi-zone-demo
    spec:
      affinity:
        nodeAffinity:
          requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
            nodeSelectorTerms:
            - matchExpressions:
              - key: topology.kubernetes.io/zone
                operator: In
                values:
                - us-east-1a
                - us-east-1b
                - us-east-1c
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: registry.k8s.io/nginx-slim:0.24

---


This is priority strength (1–100)
Weight defines priority; higher weight = more preferred
Each matching rule adds weight
Node with highest total weight wins

| Node  | Matches rule? | Weight |
| ----- | ------------- | ------ |
| node1 | yes           | 100    |
| node2 | yes           | 50     |
| node3 | no            | 0      |


More Info: https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.18/html/operator_apis/config-imageregistry-operator-openshift-io-v1

# Anti Affinity

spec:
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: myapp
    spec:
      affinity:
        podAntiAffinity:
          requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          - labelSelector:
              matchExpressions:
              - key: app
                operator: In
                values:
                - myapp
            topologyKey: kubernetes.io/hostname


Node selector
Pod chooses node by label.
Simple and exact.

Affinity / anti-affinity
Pod expresses rules or preferences.
More advanced and smarter.

Taints / tolerations
Node blocks pods unless they are allowed.
Best for isolation and reservation.






